definition: to comply with/to follow (directives)/to defer (to the judgment of superiors)
to observe/to obey/to follow/to comply with

from/through/via/to follow/to obey/to engage in (an activity)/never (in negative sentence)/(Taiwan pr. [zong4]) retainer/assistant/auxiliary/subordinate/related by common paternal grandfather or earlier ancestor

sentences.english: They are adhering to what society expects and internalising behaviours。
sentences.chinese: 他们遵从社会期望，并在行为上把这些期望内在化。

sentences.english: The result show that all the natural amino-acids will follow the rule of helix theory.
sentences.chinese: 结果表明，氨基酸类化合物也遵从螺旋理论的规律。

sentences.english: Employees don't have your typical 9-to-5 schedule.
sentences.chinese: 员工无须遵从典型的朝9晚5工作制。

sentences.english: Up to then, US artists tended to defer to their heroes in Paris.
sentences.chinese: 直到那时，美国都倾向于遵从他们在巴黎的英雄们。

sentences.english: That means well-known names and obedience to genre conventions.
sentences.chinese: 这意味着清楚明白的名称和遵从流派惯例。

sentences.english: Some laws obeyed by the beam expanding by use of the thin lens are discussed.
sentences.chinese: 讨论了用薄透镜扩束时应遵从的规律。

sentences.english: The following table generalizes some of the security requirements from common regulatory compliances.
sentences.chinese: 下面的表格归纳了常见法规遵从性的一些安全需求。

sentences.english: They are adhering to what society expects and internalising behaviours.
sentences.chinese: 他们遵从社会期望，并在行为上把这些期望内在化。

sentences.english: The statement deferred to a change in policy.
sentences.chinese: 这声明书是遵从政策的改变。

sentences.english: Even when she was angry, she observed the proprieties.
sentences.chinese: 甚至当她发怒的时候，都要遵从礼节。

sentences.english: What control mechanisms are required to ensure compliance.
sentences.chinese: 需要什么控制机制来确保遵从性。

sentences.english: Tailstock 's design also complies with a body modelling, coordinates front's fashionable outward appearance.
sentences.chinese: 车尾的设计也遵从一体造型，配合车头的时尚外观。

sentences.english: I will certainly honor your family's ways.
sentences.chinese: 既然鲍家的规矩这样，我当然会遵从。

sentences.english: For though the past it does not speak, its voiceless words all must abide.
sentences.chinese: 历史虽不能言，但它无声的话语必须遵从。

sentences.english: I did not need an operation. Instead, I did just what the doctor ordered.
sentences.chinese: 我的病用不着手术治疗，而是只需要遵从医嘱。

sentences.english: After he was admitted to comply with the wishes of Beijing Union Medical College parents.
sentences.chinese: 后遵从父母意愿考入北京协和医科大学。
